  "originalHtml": "<p data-key=\"684\"><span data-key=\"685\"><span data-offset-key=\"685:0\"><strong>In the fourth lesson</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"685:1\">, students plan their essay by selecting and ordering the evidence they will use in their essay.</span></span></p><div data-key=\"686\" class=\"BlockWrapper__block--U1QBoci undefined\"><div class=\"BlockImage__component--np2T9it\" data-alignment=\"center\"><figure class=\"BlockImage__figure--trN7ey9\"><img class=\"BlockImage__image--Oer5P08\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/com.appolearning.files/production/uploads/uploaded_file/8312ec58-20f2-4726-bc59-f00484fa88a3/kenny-eliason-Ak5c5VTch5E-unsplash.jpg\"></figure></div></div><div data-key=\"689\" class=\"BlockWrapper__block--U1QBoci undefined\"><div class=\"BlockHeader__component--Pa9vmaO\"><h2><span data-key=\"690\"><span data-offset-key=\"690:0\">Reflect and Share</span></span></h2></div></div><div data-key=\"691\" class=\"BlockWrapper__block--U1QBoci undefined\"><div class=\"BlockImage__component--np2T9it\" data-alignment=\"left\"><figure class=\"BlockImage__figure--trN7ey9\"><img class=\"BlockImage__image--Oer5P08\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/com.appolearning.files/production/uploads/uploaded_file/6f12669f-0bcf-4ad8-aeeb-e88a8234765d/Discussion_icon_2022_copy_small.png\"></figure></div></div><p data-key=\"694\"><span data-key=\"695\"><span data-offset-key=\"695:0\"><strong>Join the </strong></span></span><a target=\"_blank\" data-key=\"696\" href=\"/groups/ranking-evidence-secondary-smlc-lesson-study/46a2652f-cfc8-4050-8576-3c29158bbc1c/discussions/lesson-four/5e3a16b2-9a9b-4b1d-9fc6-27d5ac916c59\" class=\"Link__component--jdN63pa Link__theme--hyperlink--arKLCP7\"><span data-key=\"697\"><span data-offset-key=\"697:0\"><strong>Lesson Four discussion </strong></span></span></a><span data-key=\"698\"><span data-offset-key=\"698:0\"><strong>to reflect:</strong></span></span></p><ul data-key=\"699\"><li data-key=\"700\"><p data-key=\"701\"><span data-key=\"702\"><span data-offset-key=\"702:0\"><strong>If you are teaching the lesson sequence now or have already taught it</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"702:1\">, how did the evidence selection go? Were students able to select 2-4 pieces of evidence? Did they select from outside their own jigsaw source or mostly stick to the one they read? What worked well? What was challenging? Based on the planning sheets, do you think students are ready to write the full essay or do they need additional supports? </span></span></p></li><li data-key=\"703\"><p data-key=\"704\"><span data-key=\"705\"><span data-offset-key=\"705:0\"><strong>If you are teaching the lesson sequence later this year</strong></span><span data-offset-key=\"705:1\">, try out the essay planning yourself and reflect on the experience. What worked? What was challenging? What, if any, adaptations do you think you will need to make for your students?</span></span></p></li></ul><p data-key=\"706\"><span data-key=\"707\"><span data-offset-key=\"707:0\"><span data-slate-zero-width=\"n\">â€‹</span></span></span></p>"
